==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Halloween
<hw>Hal`low*een"</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧l`l⟦osl⟧*⟦emac⟧n")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The evening preceding Allhallows or All Saints' Day (November 1);
also the entire day, October 31. It is often marked by parties or
celebrations, and sometimes by pranks played by young people.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Hallowe'en, Allhallows Eve.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hallowmas</ent>⟦br⟧
